    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends the Federal Power Act to revise the criteria for a facility to qualify as a qualifying conduit hydropower facility.</p> <p>Under current law, a hydropower facility must have a capacity that does not exceed five megawatts.This bill eliminates such requirement.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill revises the timeframe for an entity to contest whether their hydroelectric facility meets the qualifying criteria.</p>]]></text>
